When a rotation of the bounding box is detected the rotation is represented as around the top-left corner as defined when the text is read in the 'natural' orientation. For example: \* when the text is horizontal it might look like: 0\-\-\--1 \| \| 3\-\-\--2 \* when it's rotated 180 degrees around the top-left corner it becomes: 2\-\-\--3 \| \| 1\-\-\--0 and the vertex order will still be (0, 1, 2, 3). |
